Sentencas: Cobalt - free perovskite oxide La0.5Ba0.5Fe0.95Mo0.05O3-delta (LBFMo) was investigated as the electrode of symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (S - SOFC) based on 300 - um - thick La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte.
Titulo: A novel cobalt-free La0.5Ba0.5Fe0.95Mo0.05O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the S - SOFC with LBFMo vertical bar LSGM vertical bar LBFMo configuration was evaluated using ambient air as oxidant and H-2 as fuel.
Titulo: A novel cobalt-free La0.5Ba0.5Fe0.95Mo0.05O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum power density (P-max) of the S - SOFC achieves as high as 0.96 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C; meanwhile, the total polarization resistance (R-pt) of the S - SOFC (including the contributions of both cathode and anode) is only similar to 0.12 Omega cm(2) .
Titulo: A novel cobalt-free La0.5Ba0.5Fe0.95Mo0.05O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Impedance spectra analysis indicates the polarization associated with anode plays a more rate - limiting role in the whole electrochemical reaction process of the S - SOFC.
Titulo: A novel cobalt-free La0.5Ba0.5Fe0.95Mo0.05O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In addition, using LBFMo as symmetric electrode, the S - SOFC also exhibits good cell stability.
Titulo: A novel cobalt-free La0.5Ba0.5Fe0.95Mo0.05O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: All results indicate that the LBFMo is a very potential candidate for S - SOFC electrode.
Titulo: A novel cobalt-free La0.5Ba0.5Fe0.95Mo0.05O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell
